 \hat f_2(k_2)|dk_2|=\hat f_1(k_1)|dk_1| \hspace{5mm} => \hspace{5mm} \hat f_2(k_2) = \hat f_1(k_1) \left|\frac{dk_1}{dk_2}\right|=\frac{1}{2\pi}\hat f_1(k_1)
=> \hspace{5mm}\hat f_2(k_2)=\frac{1}{2\pi}\int_{\mathbb{R}}f_1(x_1)e^{-ik_2 x_1}dx_1 \hspace{10mm}f_1(x_1)=\int_{\mathbb{R}}\hat f_2(k_2)e^{-ik_2 x_1}dk_2 \hspace{5mm}(2)
x_3 = 2\pi x_1
f_3(x_3)
 f_3(x_3) = f_1(x_1) \left|\frac{dx_1}{dx_3}\right|=\frac{1}{2\pi} f_1(x_1)
=> \hspace{5mm}\hat f_1(k_1)=\int_{\mathbb{R}}f_3(x_3)e^{-ik_1 x_3}dx_3 \hspace{5mm}f_3(x_3)=\frac{1}{2\pi}\int_{\mathbb{R}}\hat f_1(k_1)e^{-ik_1 x_3}dk_1 \hspace{5mm}(3)
