 f_4(x_4) = f_1(x_1) \left|\frac{dx_1}{dx_4}\right|=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} f_1(x_1)
 \hat f_4(k_4) = \hat f_1(k_1) \left|\frac{dk_1}{dk_4}\right|=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} \hat f_1(k_1)
=> \hspace{5mm}\hat f_4(k_4)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\int_{\mathbb{R}}f_4(x_4)e^{-ik_4 x_4}dx_4 \hspace{5mm}f_4(x_4)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\int_{\mathbb{R}}\hat f_4(k_4)e^{-ik_4 x_4}dk_4 \hspace{5mm}(4)
